From: CJ Damsleth <kim@damsleth.no>
Subject: [PATCH DEBUG] soc: apple: sart: isolate T8140 power handshake

This is a bring-up-only diagnostic to separate the CoastGuard power-control
handshake from accesses to the SART entry register file.  On a power-managed
SART, activate and deactivate the block using the normal driver helpers, then
finish probing without reading any entries.

Do not submit this patch.  The build harness applies it only when
SART_HANDSHAKE_ONLY=1.
---
 drivers/soc/apple/sart.c | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/soc/apple/sart.c b/drivers/soc/apple/sart.c
index d06f302e1882..92d2978c927e 100644
--- a/drivers/soc/apple/sart.c
+++ b/drivers/soc/apple/sart.c
@@ -296,6 +296,17 @@ static int apple_sart_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
+	if (sart->ops->power_managed) {
+		/*
+		 * Bring-up diagnostic: exercise only the approved CoastGuard
+		 * activate/deactivate handshake, never the SART entry window.
+		 */
+		sart_power_put(sart);
+		platform_set_drvdata(pdev, sart);
+		dev_warn(dev, "handshake-only diagnostic; entry scan skipped\n");
+		return 0;
+	}
+
 	for (i = 0; i < APPLE_SART_MAX_ENTRIES; ++i) {
 		u8 flags;
 		size_t size;
-- 
2.50.1
